OL,7,FJohnson described it as: "The
OL,8,Fcleanest, greenest bus on the streets
OL,9,Fof London by miles" .
OL,11,FBut one Labour critic called it:
OL,12,FBoris's white elephant" and the buses
OL,13,Fsoon ran into trouble after passengers
OL,14,Fcomplained of stifling heat during a
OL,15,FLondon summer.
OL,17,FThey had to be retrofitted with
OL,18,Fopening windows. The conductors were
OL,19,Flater withdrawn to save money.
